. Simon fell 0.7 percent to $155.94 yesterday in New York. Its shares have advanced 21 percent this year, compared with a 13 percent gain in the Bloomberg REIT (BBREIT) Index.\nTo contact the reporter on this story: Brian Louis in Chicago at blouis1@bloomberg.net .\nTo contact the editor responsible for this story: Kara Wetzel at kwetzel@bloomberg.net .\nMore News:\n", "update_time": "2012-10-20 21:38:56", "post_time": "2012-07-24 08:29:27", "author": "Brian Louis", "url": "http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-24/simon-property-increases-dividend-after-second-quarter-ffo-rises.html", "title": "Simon Increases Forecast After Second-Quarter FFO Rises", "post_date": "2012-07-24", "source": "Bloomberg News", "stock_index": "IBOV", "embers_id": "2d8cf4df46aeaff30ac453cc66746f15aaacaba5"}, {"content": "BR Malls Rises Most in Two Weeks as Second-Quarter Sales Jump\nBy Denyse Godoy - 2012-07-16T20:54:17Z\nBR Malls Participacoes SA (BRML3) , a Brazilian shopping mall manager, jumped the most in two weeks after reporting sales climbed more than 20 percent in the second quarter.\nShares gained 3.8 percent to 22.10 reais at the close in Sao Paulo, the most since July 3. The benchmark Bovespa index fell 1.7 percent.\nBR Malls\u2019s sales increased to 4.6 billion reais ($2.26 billion) in the April-to-June period from 3.7 billion reais in the same period last year, according to a regulatory filing today.\n\u201cInvestors expect the retail sector to slow down, but BR Malls still shows good numbers as a result of its strategy to build more shopping centers,\u201d Sandra Peres, an analyst at brokerage Coinvalores, said by phone from Sao Paulo .\nBR Malls has gained 22 percent this year, while the Bovespa declined 5.9 percent.\nTo contact the reporter on this story: Denyse Godoy in Sao Paulo at dgodoy2@bloomberg.net\nTo contact the editor responsible for this story: David Papadopoulos at papadopoulos@bloomberg.net\n", "update_time": "2012-10-20 21:39:00", "post_time": "2012-07-16 16