19s costs, including fuel and aircraft leases, are in dollars, while the majority of receivables are in reais.\nThe carrier announced June 18 that Chief Executive Officer Constantino de Oliveira Jr. was stepping down and Paulo Kakinoff, Audi AG\u2019s Brazil head, was preparing to take over as CEO on July 2. Oliveira will become chairman.\n\u201cWe have done a tremendous exercise inside the company in terms of adapting the cost structure,\u201d Pereira said. \u201cIf you have a scenario where you have a weaker real or higher fuel costs, you have to have an operation that\u2019s leaner. We are working very hard on cutting fixed costs.\u201d\nTo contact the reporters on this story: Boris Korby in New York at bkorby1@bloomberg.net ; Drew Benson in New York at abenson9@bloomberg.net\nTo contact the editor responsible for this story: David Papadopoulos at papadopoulos@bloomberg.net\nBrazil Airline Gol Cutting Workforce by 2,500\nPaolo Fridman/Bloomberg\nA Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA Boeing 737 airplane taxies on the runway at Congonhas Airport in Sao Paulo, Brazil. The Sao Paulo-based airline is firing workers and won\u2019t replace those that leave the company, Chief Financial Officer Leonardo Pereira said in an interview at Bloomberg headquarters in New York.\nA Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA Boeing 737 airplane taxies on the runway at Congonhas Airport in Sao Paulo, Brazil. The Sao Paulo-based airline is firing workers and won\u2019t replace those that leave the company, Chief Financial Officer Leonardo Pereira said in an interview at Bloomberg headquarters in New York. Photographer: Paolo Fridman/Bloomberg\nMore News:\n", "update_time": "2012-10-20 21:47:58", "post_time": "2012-06-25 17:16:12", "author": "Boris Korby , Drew Benson", "url": "http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/gol-plans-to-cut-twice-as-many-jobs-by-year-end-cfo-says-2-.html", "title": "Gol Plans to Cut Twice as Many Jobs by Year-End, CFO Says", "post_date": "2012-06-25", "source": "Bloom